The paper deals with a fundamental computational geometry problem, the potato-peeling problem, which is a well-known problem in computational geometry and falls under the category of cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also deals with finding the largest digital convex subset of a set of lattice points, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and falls under the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The algorithms presented in the paper are polynomial time algorithms, which involve computations and numerical analysis, and hence the paper can also be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also deals with the problem of finding the largest union of two digital convex subsets of a set of lattice points, which involves combinatorial optimization and can be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Overall, the most likely category is cs.CG, followed by cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, and cs.CC.
